Package: laerdal-simserver-imager
Build-Profiles: <desktop>
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, dosfstools, fdisk, fuse, libfuse2, util-linux (>= 2.37), pkexec
Recommends: udisks2
Conflicts: laerdal-simserver-imager-embedded
Description: Laerdal SimServer Imaging utility
 A user-friendly tool for creating bootable media for Laerdal SimPad and SimMan devices.

Package: laerdal-simserver-imager-embedded
Build-Profiles: <embedded>
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         dosfstools, fdisk, fuse, libfuse2, util-linux (>= 2.37), libdrm2,
         libinput10, libudev1, openssl
Conflicts: laerdal-simserver-imager
Description: Laerdal SimServer Imaging utility for embedded systems
 A user-friendly tool for creating bootable media for Laerdal SimPad and SimMan devices,
 optimized for embedded systems.
 .
 This version is specifically designed for embedded systems:
  - Uses linuxfb for direct rendering (no desktop environment required)
  - Optimized for network-based installation
  - Smaller memory footprint for embedded applications
  - Supports DRM/KMS rendering

Package: laerdal-simserver-imager-cli
Build-Profiles: <cli>
Architecture: amd64 arm64 armhf
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         dosfstools, fdisk, fuse, libfuse2, util-linux (>= 2.37)
Conflicts: laerdal-simserver-imager, laerdal-simserver-imager-embedded
Description: Laerdal SimServer Imaging utility (command-line only)
 A command-line tool for creating bootable media for Laerdal SimPad and SimMan devices.
 .
 This version is optimized for command-line operation:
  - No GUI components - CLI mode only
  - Minimal dependencies (Qt Core only)
  - Perfect for headless servers, automation and scripting
  - Smaller package size and memory footprint
  - Most imaging functionality available via command line
  - Ideal for scripting and CI/CD pipelines
